name: float_f32_smallest_positive_subnormal
description: |
  This is the smallest positive non-zero binary32 value, 2^-149. Hardware,
  compiler modes, or accelerated kernels using flush-to-zero may turn it into
  positive zero, changing equality, loop termination, underflow behavior, and
  division results. Its encoding also exercises gradual underflow.
format: hex
decode-as: f32
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f32"
  - "subnormal"
  - "underflow"
---
01 00 00 00 # 0x00000001: 2^-149
